<plot>An essay-film that reconstructs the colourful past of a family of puppeteers (the filmmakers' family) in Paraguay, one of South America's poorest and lesser known countries. Accompanied by a classical guitar soundtrack, the film explores the survival of this art form, celebrates the work, creativity and passion of artists, and captures the universal magic and timelessness of puppetry.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?155311</url></doc>
